[lyottia_conversation_06_couple_2_female_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The entire blockade is nonsense. Whoever rules here next, they're going to need our hands working on their land. Slaying citizens helps no one. The only ones in danger are soldiers and nobles.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_couple_2_male_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Last time a lord challenged another lord in this realm, villages of Old Palisade and Ripplefields were turned to dust. The army was then marched towards Broomnest, aiming to burn it down as well. If it wasn't for those insane orc raiders living nearby, the army would have succeeded. They say that the people of Broomnest have formed bond with orc, and have lived in peace ever since. Would you believe that? I fear there will not be any orc army rescuing us if lord Neezethos decided to strike here.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_couple_2_male_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "It's a shame that our lords cannot solve their feuds by duelling, and involve armies and commoners instead.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_drunk_guards_wife_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Are you here to complain about what my husband or his brother did? Spare me your me your whining, living with them is worse than anything they could have done to you. They're getting drunk with our worthless guard captain somewhere in the mountains, so enjoy your stay they're gone.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_drunk_guards_wife_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Leave me alone. I am not in mood to talk right now.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_dwarf_herbalist_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Greeting! An adventurous type, I see. Care for a little lesson in herbs? Don't asnwer, please, you will receive one anyway. Free of charge of couse. Remember, petals of Flame-Woven Rose soothe pain. Just place them on your wound. Juice from Torreckhead Fern prevents infection. Drinking it might kill you, however. Last but not least, no headache ever resisted Honey Kiss Berries. It is not the berries that help however - it is the thorns. Just chew a few of them for duration of average spellcaster's Magic Shield, and you'll be able to think clearly again. Do not try to eat them. They're harmless, but the experience is not pleasant. No need to thank me, youngster, just follow my advice the next time you're wrecked after fight.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_dwarf_herbalist_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "None of the local farmers grow herbs. What will they do when a someone gets sick or injured? Luckily, they have me.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_1_daughter_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Mia just won't wear anything besides her good dress. She's gonna have it tattered soon if she keeps working the field in it. I would be pitty though, the dress suits her nicely.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_1_daughter_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I must sound silly to you that I'm concerned about a dress, given the current situation. However, that dress means a lot to my sister, and my sister is most precious to me. There's no treasure like family in this world, even with all their flaws.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_daughter_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Our livestock is demanding in terms of care, but we should definitely look to expand. What a better way to feed our village and earn enough wealth to buy pretty things?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_daughter_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I think we should definitely get more chickens. Or a cat, perhaps. A mice-hunting operative would certainly help our farm.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_1_father_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Sirmanith and Mia are playing with the chickens again, are they? I'm not mad thought, the chickens seem to prosper better when my daughters spend time with them. They're definitely being more useful than my miserable fool of a son getting drunk with the captain of local guard.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_1_father_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "My children are too careless. They will struggle in the events that are upon us. But how could I strip that from them? It's a blessing in this world where we are but playthings of lords and monsters.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_brother_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The supplies and resources of Meadow Steps may seem impressive, but in many ways we depend on trade. We may have fields, seeds and water, but how will we replace our hoes, pitchforks and rakes when they go rusty? The closest mine is Axeshatter mine near Needlewood. Without guards and caravans patrolling the roads, we won't be receiving any metal materials. We need to be prepared to only use wooden tools. But most people here solve their problems by drinking.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_brother_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "If my brother and sister don't start helping me with the fields soon, we'll be starving in a few months.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_brother_2_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Athnos thinks he's all charming and impressive, towering above us and smiling wide. But I know better. I can see the hypocrisy of his pose.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_brother_2_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I bet I could take Athnos with no effort.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_family_2_sister_first]
