	[text*]
	{
		choice = buy_packmule;
		screen_text = "Greetings, fellow traveler. Is your stay as dull as mine? Ever since the blockade took place, this village has been just a gloomy promenade of boredom. Luckily, I have my traggs to be my company. Despite that, I am actually here to sell them. As much as I hate to get rid of them right now, how about you buy one or two of them? I will need the money once travelling is possible again.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_06_tragg_shop_mules]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = buy_packmule;
		screen_text = "I'm going to miss those playful adorables, but I have already accepted that I'm going to say goodbye to them. Are you here for purchase?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_06_tragg_shop_no_mules]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I'm going to have to come up with some other pastime. Perhaps I might take some lessons in nature magic. If I ever breed a new batch, keeping their health with my own spells might be much cheaper than it is to hire someone else to do it.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_priest_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Welcome, traveler. I'm afraid I'm too busy to provide you with temple services. There have been reports of the dead rising from their graves. I try to communicate with the divines, but they are silent about it. Luckily, here we burn our dead and spread them in forests, so we're safe. I worry about other villages and the cities. The dead outnumber the living, you know.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_priest_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I must keep listening, in case the divines have something to say about the dead.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_seck_guide_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Well, well, well, look who made it all the way to the town. Last time I saw you, a lazy grumpy home-sitter was standing in front of me. Now I see a proper adventurer wearing actual armor and with actual weapon in hands. You have my admiration. Oh I love to climb. I avoided those dreadful caves by far. Insects are not quite the kind of company I enjoy. You should try that track some time. It took me through part of the minotaur kingdom. You would not believe the kind of treasures an average minotaur carries with them. Who am I? The same question again? For now, I'm someone entertained by observing your progress, is that not enough? I suggest you keep looking for your next adventure. You have reached the town, fine. That's a milestone, but there's a certain lack of purpose, don't you think? We should put you up to something. You have already heard about the blockade, right? One lord's armies are blocking other lord's villages from freely travelling, and therefore delivering supplies to that lord's armies. That sounds like serious preparion for a war with some starting advantage, right? Greed of human lords endangering poor villagers, what better quest could an adventurer ask for, right? So, what's the waiting about? Grab a weapon and take on the villain lord!";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_seck_guide_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Still skulking about? Right, make sure you are properly equiped. I'm sure there's a lot more trouble waiting for you before you finally confront the lord.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_bows_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "This blockade situation is stressful, but at least I have time to carve my bows with precision. It's not good when you're on the cart shaking all the time. You end up cutting yourself more often than the wood.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_bows_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Can I fashion you a new bow?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_general_local_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Please, come and see my wares. I know that the traveling merchant spreads gossip about me, but how about you see for yourself what the quality of my goods really is?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_general_local_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Is there any other way I can help you?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_general_travel_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Please, step closer. We haven't been able to obtain new goods since the blockade, but we are excelently supplied anyway. Way better than the local store is. I suggest you don't even bother visiting them. Come see my wares, you'll be pleasantly surprised.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_general_travel_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Come and unveil what I have for sale.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_magic_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "With caravan stuck here, I have nothing to do, so I work on this pillar. I want to create a magical glowing statue and leave it here once we leave. It will be my way to thank the villagers for the hospitality. I haven't even decided what it's going to be. Wanna see my wares?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_shop_magic_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "Wanna see my wares again? I can use a break from pillar-shaping.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_spider_watch_quest_started_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "There's a darkness here preying on us, out of everybody's sight. Village's attention is drawn to the blockade, but there is more immediate danger for us. In recent days, a few farm animals have gone missing. Others blame the Claw and Taugrims, or maybe those little creepy tribesmen, and the lack of guards here. But I have seen the real thief. Every night, a huge spider ceeps into the village and steals our animals for his dinner. I tried talking to the guards, but they looked at me as if I was mad. So I decided to keep watch here in case they show up during daylight. It would be more reasonable to keep guard in night, but...I am not that brave. I'm afraid thing will get worse as soon as that spider breeds and spreads its youngling on the countryside. I'm sure it resides just beyond this bridge. If you find a way to climb the cliffs, it will live in some of the caverns there. Would you helps and slay it? Oh, and one more thing. There are two of them. I assume you will need to visit two caverns.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_spider_watch_quest_started_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "My prayers are with you, adventurer.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_spider_watch_quest_ended_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "You have done a heroic thing for Meadow Steps. It shall never be forgotten. Your name will be remembered.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_spider_watch_quest_ended_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "My sleep is easy now. May yours be, too.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_widow_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The stupid corrupt guard captain will be the downfall of all of us. While he's gone, I'm going to asssume his position. And replace him when he comes back. My late husband was the captain before him and taught be how to a real captain.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_widow_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "So long, traveler.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_before_step_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Greetings, young one. You have made it safely through the caverns then? This warms my heart greatly, for it is in the grip of fear right now. We did not hesitate and traveled here to negotiate a trade offer, as this is the the town nearest to our home. The residents call it Meadow Steps, I believe. We are waiting for our Scout, Akkera, to report his observations of the local customs. We will have to concince locals that we are not the savage beasts they will surely see in us.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_before_step_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I would ask you to speak in our behalf, but this cannot come from your own initiative. Perhaps if you spoke to local guards, they might ask you to scout the surroundings. The monster situation here is alarming, these humans are much weaker fighters than we are. If you were able to pretend that you run into us randomly, you might speak up for us and the locals would be more likely to trust you.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_after_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The guards asked you to investigate this cliff in specific? Who knows, perhaps we were not careful enough with our cargo and one of them caught a glimpse of us? Either way, we need Akkera's observations anyway. Only a fool comes to the negotation table without knowing the other party first. We were expecting to hear from her a day ago, and I fear something bad might have happened. Could you go around the town and ask guardsmen or other men of arms if they saw something unusual? I doubt that a citizen without military experience could ever see a hassat scout when he wishes not to be seen.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_after_step_2]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Please, ask around the town if they have seen something unusual. I am deeply concerned about Akkera's fate.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_after_step_3]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "You bring bittersweet news, friend. Akkera knew the risks of this mission and had accepted them voluntarily. But that doesn't make the pain at my heart any easier. I guided and trained her since she was a little kitten. But such is the cost of survival of the Taeries clan. We will meet the town's representatives at the time presented, bearing no weapons. Hopefully the second encounter of our nations will take better course than the first one.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_negotiator_after_step_4]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "You have done great deeds for the Taerie tribe once again. Songs will be sung about you around the fires from now on for eternity.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_1_before_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Hail, friend.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_1_after_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Now is the right time to arrange negotiations.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_1_after_step_2]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I wonder what Akkera is up to. A good spy is never late.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_1_after_step_3]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Forgiveness is a virtue. If we show it, perhaps they will be more willing to trade with us. Akkera would have wanted it that way.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_1_after_step_4]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "**Purrrrrr** Your face is always a welcome sight, friend.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_2_before_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Hello friend. You have fared well since you last met our tribe, haven't you?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_2_after_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I don't really like this plan that much, with you pretending that you have met us randomly and all. It's a small lie and follows a noble purpose, but I still feel uneasy.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_2_after_step_2]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I suspect you will find Akkera as someone's trophy. Althought I hope you won't.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_2_after_step_3]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I feared as much. She was skillful and brave, but sometimes too daring.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_hassat_guard_2_after_step_4]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I just wish Akkera was here to rejoice with us.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_town_guard_before_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Greetings, traveler. It is unusual for anyone to come from that direction. With the blockade of roads taking place, we are stretched too thin and we cannot maintain the monster population levels as low as usual. Not too long ago, I even noticed some stealthy figures in the bushes. Listen, before you unpack yourself in the village, how about you investigate it? Just follow the path up the cliff right here.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_town_guard_after_step_1]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "If you haven't explored the cliff yet, please do. I am concerned about security of the village.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_town_guard_after_step_2]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Hmmph, no, I haven't really seen a creature you describe. The stealthy figures I mentioned earlier were too swift for me to see them clearly. But I remember that Yagraz mentioned some unusual fresh kill. Enter the village, climb up the path, pass the pig farm and turn right to climb up the cliff. Follow the path until T-shaped crossroad. Turn left, pass the tent of tragg-selling lady and follow the path further. You should be able to find him there.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_town_guard_after_step_3]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "A negotiation? Yagraz overestimates his importance if he thinks he can arrange that for the whole town. But still, it is reasonable to hear those beings out. With the blockade going on, any potential ally must not be turned down without careful consideration.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_town_guard_after_step_4]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "We will gather the representatives and meet them in no time. Thank you, friend.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_before_step_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Hail friend. Have you killed anything interesting lately?";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_before_step_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I had no idea hassat were game in these parts. I might have to investigate further.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_1_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "The guards asked you to work for free and you agreed?? Clearly, both of you are desperate.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_1_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I'm just kidding. Ever since the blockade, I try to help with reducing the taugrim and phrak population.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_2]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I thought the creature was some hungry beast. And you're saying it was a sentient soul sent here to form friendly relations with our town? Am deeply ashamed. I am not soft, I know this could be some sort of trap. But there's always a possibility it's not. The blockade will push us to the limits of our supplies. Hassat are great hunters. If they could supply us with meat, we might make it event if the blockade lasts for years. Moreover, we could join forces in fighting the monsters on the town's outskirts. Tell them I will assemble the village's representatives and meet them on midday two days from now on.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_3]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Deliver my message, please. It is of uttermost importance they receive it on time.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_4_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I am relieved to hear they agreed to meet us. With so many troubles about, we need powerful friends.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_06_taerie_quest_adventurer_after_step_4_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "You have done this village an unforgettable service, friend. Thank you.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}